DSS-USOD
Source code for our paper Learning Dynamic Structural Specialization for Underwater Salient Object Detection
ArXiv Link: https://arxiv.org/abs/2506.19472
Authors: Lin Hong, Xin Wang, Yihao Li, Xia Wang
Maintainer: Lin Hong
Contact Email: eelinhong@ust.hk
We are open to research collaboration and recruiting self-motivated students. If you are interested in underwater salient object detection, underwater vision, and related deep learning topics, please feel free to contact us via email.

---
Overview
DSS-USOD is a simple yet strong baseline model for underwater salient object detection (USOD). The model adopts a concise encoder-decoder hybrid architecture, which takes Transformer as the core module of the encoder and convolution as the core module of the decoder, achieving superior performance on complex underwater scene benchmarks.


---
Environment Requirements
Python 3.8
Pytorch 1.6.0
Torchvision 0.7.0

